  "text": "a phase-shifted (n−1)-dimensional harmonic (Fig. 3(c) , red curve), where proj Π ω is the perpendicular projection of ω onto Π, and the phase shift 2πdn · ω depends on both the distance from Π to the origin and the relative orientation of n and ω. Note that proj Π ω is the component of ω parallel to Π, and n · ω is the length of the component of ω perpendicular to Π. We now observe that, because of the phase shift ( Fig. 3(a,c) , φ s ), the product of the sliced Gaussian (Eqn. 3) and the sliced harmonic (Eqn. 4) cannot be expressed as a Gabor kernel (Eqn. 1). In other words, the Gabor kernel of [CITATION_1] is not closed under slicing.",
